The paper discusses a compositional analysis technique for formal probabilistic models of gossip protocols in wireless sensor networks. This topic is closely related to network protocols and communication systems, which are covered by the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-categories. The paper also involves probabilistic models and simulation theory, which fall under the cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses algebraic laws for estimating the performance of gossip networks, which is related to the cs.PF (Performance) sub-category.
